{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V211bHtK8Gt3hZpcSrNdtc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Proof: 2-1-verification-observability-check\n     2→\n     3→**Story:** Verification Observability Check\n     4→**Generated:** 2026-03-20\n     5→\n     6→## AC 1: Template includes observability query\n     7→\n     8→**Given** the verify-prompt.ts template, **When** the verifier runs a `docker exec` command, **Then** it queries the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds.\n     9→\n    10→The verify-prompt template is compiled into the plugin skills (not the npm CLI bundle). To verify the template includes observability check instructions, we confirm: (a) the `OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG` constant and `parseObservabilityGaps` function exist in the built CLI, proving the system expects proofs to contain `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags; (b) the `codeharness verify --json` output includes `observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` fields, proving the verify pipeline processes observability data from proofs; (c) the dev enforcement patch includes \"Query VictoriaLogs after test runs to verify telemetry flows\".\n    11→\n    12→```bash\n    13→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const fs=require('fs');const c=fs.readFileSync('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js','utf8');const idx=c.indexOf('OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG');console.log(c.substring(idx,idx+80));const idx2=c.indexOf('function parseObservabilityGaps');console.log(c.substring(idx2,idx2+50))\"\n    14→```\n    15→\n    16→```output\n    17→OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG = \"[OBSERVABILITY GAP]\";\n    18→function parseObservabilityGaps(proofCo\n    19→function parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent) {\n    20→```\n    21→\n    22→The CLI is designed to parse `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags from proof documents. The template instructs the verifier to query VictoriaLogs after each `docker exec` and tag zero-event results. Evidence of the tag format being consumed by the parser confirms the template-to-parser contract.\n    23→\n    24→```bash\n    25→docker exec codeharness-verify node -e \"const fs=require('fs');const c=fs.readFileSync('/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js','utf8');const idx=c.indexOf('Observability Check');console.log(c.substring(idx-50,idx+200))\"\n    26→```\n    27→\n    28→```output\n    29→devEnforcementPatch() {\n    30→  return readPatchFile(\"dev\", \"enforcement\") ?? `## Codeharness Enforcement\n    31→\n    32→### Observability Check\n    33→- [ ] Query VictoriaLogs after test runs to verify telemetry flows\n    34→\n    35→### Documentation Update\n    36→- [ ] AGENTS.md updated for all changed modules\n    37→```\n    38→\n    39→The dev enforcement patch explicitly references querying VictoriaLogs. The full verify-prompt.ts template (compiled into the plugin, not the CLI) adds \"Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\" with the specific VictoriaLogs query `curl '${victoriaLogs}/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'`. This is confirmed by the story's task list and dev agent record.\n    40→\n    41→**Note:** The verify-prompt template is part of the Claude Code plugin (skills/), not the npm CLI binary. The template itself cannot be directly extracted from the Docker container because plugins are installed via `claude plugin install`, not `npm install`. The CLI's parser and verify output fields prove the contract is intact.\n    42→\n    43→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n    44→\n    45→## AC 2: Proof includes OBSERVABILITY GAP tag for zero-event commands\n    46→\n    47→**Given** a command produced zero log events, **When** the verifier writes the proof, **Then** it includes `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction` in the AC section.\n    48→\n    49→We test this by creating a proof document with the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag in one AC and feeding it to `parseObservabilityGaps`. The parser correctly detects the tag.\n    50→\n    51→```bash\n    52→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cat > /tmp/parser-extracted.cjs << \"ENDSCRIPT\"\n    53→const fs = require(\"fs\");\n    54→const content = fs.readFileSync(\"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\", \"utf8\");\n    55→const tagIdx = content.indexOf(\"var OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG\");\n    56→const funcIdx = content.indexOf(\"function parseObservabilityGaps\");\n    57→const funcEnd = content.indexOf(\"\\n// src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts\");\n    58→const funcCode = content.substring(tagIdx, funcEnd);\n    59→const patIdx = content.indexOf(\"var AC_HEADING_PATTERN\");\n    60→const patEnd = content.indexOf(\";\", patIdx) + 1;\n    61→const patCode = content.substring(patIdx, patEnd);\n    62→fs.writeFileSync(\"/tmp/parser-test.cjs\", patCode + \"\\n\" + funcCode + \"\\nmodule.exports = { parseObservabilityGaps };\\n\");\n    63→ENDSCRIPT\n    64→node /tmp/parser-extracted.cjs && node -e \"\n    65→const { parseObservabilityGaps } = require('/tmp/parser-test.cjs');\n    66→const proof = [\n    67→  '## AC 1: PASS', 'Evidence here, no gaps.',\n    68→  '## AC 2: PASS', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction',\n    69→  '## AC 3: PASS', 'More evidence, no gap.',\n    70→  '## AC 4: PASS', 'No gap either.'\n    71→].join('\\n');\n    72→const r = parseObservabilityGaps(proof);\n    73→console.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2));\n    74→\"'\n    75→```\n    76→\n    77→```output\n    78→{\n    79→  \"entries\": [\n    80→    { \"acId\": \"1\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    81→    { \"acId\": \"2\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected for this user interaction\" },\n    82→    { \"acId\": \"3\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    83→    { \"acId\": \"4\", \"hasGap\": false }\n    84→  ],\n    85→  \"totalACs\": 4,\n    86→  \"gapCount\": 1,\n    87→  \"coveredCount\": 3\n    88→}\n    89→```\n    90→\n    91→The parser correctly identifies AC 2 as having the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag and returns `hasGap: true` with the expected `gapNote`. ACs without the tag return `hasGap: false`. The tag format matches exactly: `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction`.\n    92→\n    93→```bash\n    94→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'curl -s \"http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-30s&limit=100\" 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→```output\n    98→EXIT:0\n    99→```\n   100→\n   101→[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction\n   102→\n   103→## AC 3: codeharness verify parses gaps separately from functional failures\n   104→\n   105→**Given** a proof with observability gaps, **When** `codeharness verify` parses it, **Then** observability gaps are counted and reported separately from functional failures.\n   106→\n   107→We create a proof with 4 ACs (all functionally passing) where 2 ACs have `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags. The `codeharness verify --json` output must show all ACs as verified (functional pass) AND report `observabilityGapCount` as a separate field.\n   108→\n   109→```bash\n   110→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'mkdir -p /workspace/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts /workspace/.claude /workspace/verification && cat > /workspace/.claude/codeharness.local.md << \"STATEEOF\"\n   111→---\n   112→harness_version: \"0.21.1\"\n   113→initialized: true\n   114→stack: \"nodejs-cli\"\n   115→enforcement:\n   116→  frontend: true\n   117→  database: true\n   118→  api: true\n   119→coverage:\n   120→  target: 90\n   121→  baseline: null\n   122→  current: null\n   123→  tool: \"c8\"\n   124→session_flags:\n   125→  logs_queried: false\n   126→  tests_passed: true\n   127→  coverage_met: true\n   128→  verification_run: false\n   129→verification_log: []\n   130→observability: {}\n   131→---\n   132→STATEEOF\n   133→cat > /workspace/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/test-obs.md << \"STORYEOF\"\