{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01VZzTU4mmMhYGm23E5TDdo1","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The verify command thinks there are 8 ACs but the story only has 4. The issue is that the verify command is somehow parsing more ACs from the story file. Let me check - maybe it's counting the ACs in the story file differently, or the story file has additional AC-like items. Let me look at the story file again to count: it has 4 numbered ACs (1-4). But the `codeharness verify` command might be counting the \"Verification Requirements\" checkboxes too. Or maybe it's counting ACs from the proof differently.\n\nWait - the proof has sections: \"AC 1\", \"AC 2\", \"AC 3\", \"AC 4\", and also \"Observability Summary\" and \"Verification Summary\". \n\nThose last two shouldn't be counted as ACs. So the verify command is probably picking up extra items from the story file - maybe the checkboxes under \"Verification Requirements\" or other checkbox-like structures are being counted as acceptance criteria when they shouldn't be. I'm wondering if the verify command is parsing the story file differently than I'm counting manually—maybe it's detecting additional AC sections or parsing them in a way I haven't considered. Let me check the verify command's actual behavior or look at how it counts ACs in the story to understand where the discrepancy between 4 and 8 is coming from.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":246,"cache_read_input_tokens":63765,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":246},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8712fecb-812b-48fe-bd95-ad6ae808447d","uuid":"78c5b927-d160-46ab-b542-cce26f1b2257"}
