{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V8v2h74wqCH35anAnyWaKQ","type":"tool_result","content":"    50→\n    51→```bash\n    52→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cat > /tmp/parser-extracted.cjs << \"ENDSCRIPT\"\n    53→const fs = require(\"fs\");\n    54→const content = fs.readFileSync(\"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\", \"utf8\");\n    55→const tagIdx = content.indexOf(\"var OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG\");\n    56→const funcIdx = content.indexOf(\"function parseObservabilityGaps\");\n    57→const funcEnd = content.indexOf(\"\\n// src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts\");\n    58→const funcCode = content.substring(tagIdx, funcEnd);\n    59→const patIdx = content.indexOf(\"var AC_HEADING_PATTERN\");\n    60→const patEnd = content.indexOf(\";\", patIdx) + 1;\n    61→const patCode = content.substring(patIdx, patEnd);\n    62→fs.writeFileSync(\"/tmp/parser-test.cjs\", patCode + \"\\n\" + funcCode + \"\\nmodule.exports = { parseObservabilityGaps };\\n\");\n    63→ENDSCRIPT\n    64→node /tmp/parser-extracted.cjs && node -e \"\n    65→const { parseObservabilityGaps } = require('/tmp/parser-test.cjs');\n    66→const proof = [\n    67→  '## AC 1: PASS', 'Evidence here, no gaps.',\n    68→  '## AC 2: PASS', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction',\n    69→  '## AC 3: PASS', 'More evidence, no gap.',\n    70→  '## AC 4: PASS', 'No gap either.'\n    71→].join('\\n');\n    72→const r = parseObservabilityGaps(proof);\n    73→console.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2));\n    74→\"'\n    75→```\n    76→\n    77→```output\n    78→{\n    79→  \"entries\": [\n    80→    { \"acId\": \"1\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    81→    { \"acId\": \"2\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected for this user interaction\" },\n    82→    { \"acId\": \"3\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    83→    { \"acId\": \"4\", \"hasGap\": false }\n    84→  ],\n    85→  \"totalACs\": 4,\n    86→  \"gapCount\": 1,\n    87→  \"coveredCount\": 3\n    88→}\n    89→```\n    90→\n    91→The parser correctly identifies AC 2 as having the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag and returns `hasGap: true` with the expected `gapNote`. ACs without the tag return `hasGap: false`. The tag format matches exactly: `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction`.\n    92→\n    93→```bash\n    94→docker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'curl -s \"http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-30s&limit=100\" 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n    95→```\n    96→\n    97→```output\n    98→EXIT:0\n    99→```"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8712fecb-812b-48fe-bd95-ad6ae808447d","uuid":"6c6a167b-5890-474b-b341-91fd39faaef9","timestamp":"2026-03-20T05:44:11.705Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/2-1-verification-observability-check-proof.md","content":"\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'cat > /tmp/parser-extracted.cjs << \"ENDSCRIPT\"\nconst fs = require(\"fs\");\nconst content = fs.readFileSync(\"/usr/local/lib/node_modules/codeharness/dist/index.js\", \"utf8\");\nconst tagIdx = content.indexOf(\"var OBSERVABILITY_GAP_TAG\");\nconst funcIdx = content.indexOf(\"function parseObservabilityGaps\");\nconst funcEnd = content.indexOf(\"\\n// src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts\");\nconst funcCode = content.substring(tagIdx, funcEnd);\nconst patIdx = content.indexOf(\"var AC_HEADING_PATTERN\");\nconst patEnd = content.indexOf(\";\", patIdx) + 1;\nconst patCode = content.substring(patIdx, patEnd);\nfs.writeFileSync(\"/tmp/parser-test.cjs\", patCode + \"\\n\" + funcCode + \"\\nmodule.exports = { parseObservabilityGaps };\\n\");\nENDSCRIPT\nnode /tmp/parser-extracted.cjs && node -e \"\nconst { parseObservabilityGaps } = require('/tmp/parser-test.cjs');\nconst proof = [\n  '## AC 1: PASS', 'Evidence here, no gaps.',\n  '## AC 2: PASS', '[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction',\n  '## AC 3: PASS', 'More evidence, no gap.',\n  '## AC 4: PASS', 'No gap either.'\n].join('\\n');\nconst r = parseObservabilityGaps(proof);\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify(r, null, 2));\n\"'\n```\n\n```output\n{\n  \"entries\": [\n    { \"acId\": \"1\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"2\", \"hasGap\": true, \"gapNote\": \"No log events detected for this user interaction\" },\n    { \"acId\": \"3\", \"hasGap\": false },\n    { \"acId\": \"4\", \"hasGap\": false }\n  ],\n  \"totalACs\": 4,\n  \"gapCount\": 1,\n  \"coveredCount\": 3\n}\n```\n\nThe parser correctly identifies AC 2 as having the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag and returns `hasGap: true` with the expected `gapNote`. ACs without the tag return `hasGap: false`. The tag format matches exactly: `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction`.\n\n```bash\ndocker exec codeharness-verify sh -c 'curl -s \"http://localhost:9428/select/logsql/query?query=*&start=-30s&limit=100\" 2>&1; echo \"EXIT:$?\"'\n```\n\n```output\nEXIT:0\n```","numLines":50,"startLine":50,"totalLines":241}}}
