{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WiD5eBECRujAdTqfFA1eKx","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-19\n     2→\n     3→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-19T09:00Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Epic 0.5 appeared:** The create-story agent added a new Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display) to sprint-status.yaml despite being told not to modify it. This is a workflow compliance issue.\n     6→- **AC #1 integration risk:** Verifying that the verifier queries observability after docker exec requires a live verification session — hard to test in isolation.\n     7→- **Tag coupling risk:** `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag format is a convention between prompt template and parser regex. If verifier (Claude) doesn't emit exact format, parser won't detect it.\n     8→- **Naming confusion:** Epic 2 retrospective file references a different Epic 2 from a previous sprint.\n     9→\n    10→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — dev-story (2026-03-19T09:08Z)\n    11→\n    12→- **Import boundary violation (fixed):** `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` directly. Fixed to use barrel import.\n    13→- **logEventCount is binary:** Set to 0 or 1 based on gap presence, not actual log event count. Parser only detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag presence.\n    14→- **VerifyResult field additions are breaking:** All existing `VerifyResult` constructions needed updating (5 files). Optional fields with defaults would reduce churn.\n    15→- **Task 2.4 no-op:** No new config fields needed — existing `observabilityEndpoints.victoriaLogs` already sufficient.\n    16→\n    17→### 2-1-verification-observability-check — code-review (2026-03-19T09:15Z)\n    18→\n    19→- **HIGH: saveRuntimeCoverage was dead code** — never called from production, only tested. Runtime coverage would never persist to sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n    20→- **MEDIUM: verify.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — command always reported 0 observability gaps regardless of proof content. Fixed.\n    21→- **MEDIUM: verifier-session.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — same pattern as verify.ts. Fixed.\n    22→- **LOW (not fixed): Binary logEventCount** — always 0 or 1, not actual log counts. Tech debt.\n    23→- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated coverage math** — verify/index.ts duplicates computeRuntimeCoverage logic.\n    24→- **LOW (not fixed): Silent catch blocks** — gap parsing errors silently swallowed in 3 locations.\n    25→- **Architecture: Hardcoded CWD** — verifyStory() calls saveRuntimeCoverage with '.' as projectDir, assumes CWD is project root.\n    26→- **Architecture: Triple gap parsing** — 3 separate locations independently parse gaps. Should be centralized.\n    27→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8712fecb-812b-48fe-bd95-ad6ae808447d","uuid":"f1c35bff-09a4-4c1b-b88f-b0790b9a7008","timestamp":"2026-03-20T05:45:46.437Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-19\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — create-story (2026-03-19T09:00Z)\n\n- **Epic 0.5 appeared:** The create-story agent added a new Epic 0.5 (Stream-JSON Live Activity Display) to sprint-status.yaml despite being told not to modify it. This is a workflow compliance issue.\n- **AC #1 integration risk:** Verifying that the verifier queries observability after docker exec requires a live verification session — hard to test in isolation.\n- **Tag coupling risk:** `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag format is a convention between prompt template and parser regex. If verifier (Claude) doesn't emit exact format, parser won't detect it.\n- **Naming confusion:** Epic 2 retrospective file references a different Epic 2 from a previous sprint.\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — dev-story (2026-03-19T09:08Z)\n\n- **Import boundary violation (fixed):** `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` directly. Fixed to use barrel import.\n- **logEventCount is binary:** Set to 0 or 1 based on gap presence, not actual log event count. Parser only detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag presence.\n- **VerifyResult field additions are breaking:** All existing `VerifyResult` constructions needed updating (5 files). Optional fields with defaults would reduce churn.\n- **Task 2.4 no-op:** No new config fields needed — existing `observabilityEndpoints.victoriaLogs` already sufficient.\n\n### 2-1-verification-observability-check — code-review (2026-03-19T09:15Z)\n\n- **HIGH: saveRuntimeCoverage was dead code** — never called from production, only tested. Runtime coverage would never persist to sprint-state.json. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: verify.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — command always reported 0 observability gaps regardless of proof content. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: verifier-session.ts hardcoded 0 gaps** — same pattern as verify.ts. Fixed.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Binary logEventCount** — always 0 or 1, not actual log counts. Tech debt.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Duplicated coverage math** — verify/index.ts duplicates computeRuntimeCoverage logic.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Silent catch blocks** — gap parsing errors silently swallowed in 3 locations.\n- **Architecture: Hardcoded CWD** — verifyStory() calls saveRuntimeCoverage with '.' as projectDir, assumes CWD is project root.\n- **Architecture: Triple gap parsing** — 3 separate locations independently parse gaps. Should be centralized.\n","numLines":27,"startLine":1,"totalLines":27}}}
