{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_014UTsScfVgS1RCSBbzk3WQz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 2.1: Verification Observability Check\n     2→\n     3→Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a verifier,\n    10→I want to check that every docker exec command produces log events in the observability stack,\n    11→so that silent code paths are detected during verification.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. **Given** the verify-prompt.ts template, **When** the verifier runs a `docker exec` command, **Then** it queries the observability backend for log events from the last 30 seconds. <!-- verification: integration-required -->\n    16→2. **Given** a command produced zero log events, **When** the verifier writes the proof, **Then** it includes `[OBSERVABILITY GAP] No log events detected for this user interaction` in the AC section. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. **Given** a proof with observability gaps, **When** `codeharness verify` parses it, **Then** observability gaps are counted and reported separately from functional failures. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. **Given** 10 ACs verified and 7 produced log events, **When** runtime coverage is computed, **Then** runtime coverage = 70%. <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→\n    20→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    21→\n    22→- [x] Task 1: Add runtime coverage types to `src/modules/observability/types.ts` (AC: #3, #4)\n    23→  - [x] 1.1: Add `RuntimeCoverageEntry` interface with fields: `acId: string`, `logEventsDetected: boolean`, `logEventCount: number`, `gapNote?: string`\n    24→  - [x] 1.2: Add `RuntimeCoverageResult` interface with fields: `entries: RuntimeCoverageEntry[]`, `totalACs: number`, `acsWithLogs: number`, `coveragePercent: number`\n    25→  - [x] 1.3: Add `RuntimeCoverageState` interface with fields: `coveragePercent: number`, `lastValidationTimestamp: string`, `modulesWithTelemetry: number`, `totalModules: number`, `telemetryDetected: boolean` -- aligned with architecture Decision 2\n    26→  - [x] 1.4: Extend `ObservabilityCoverageState` to include optional `runtime?: RuntimeCoverageState` section (additive, does not break Story 1.3)\n    27→  - [x] 1.5: Extend `CoverageTargets` to include optional `runtimeTarget?: number` (default 60)\n    28→\n    29→- [x] Task 2: Update verify-prompt.ts template with observability check instructions (AC: #1)\n    30→  - [x] 2.1: Add an observability check section after the \"Verify Each AC\" step instructing the verifier to query the observability backend after each `docker exec` command\n    31→  - [x] 2.2: Include the specific query template: `curl '${victoriaLogs}/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'`\n    32→  - [x] 2.3: Include the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag format for zero-event results\n    33→  - [x] 2.4: Update `VerifyPromptConfig` if any new config fields are needed\n    34→  - [x] 2.5: Update existing verify-prompt tests to cover the new template section\n    35→\n    36→- [x] Task 3: Implement observability gap parser in `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` (AC: #2, #3)\n    37→  - [x] 3.1: Add `parseObservabilityGaps(proofContent: string): ObservabilityGapResult` function that scans proof text for `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags\n    38→  - [x] 3.2: Return per-AC observability gap presence (which ACs have the gap tag)\n    39→  - [x] 3.3: Ensure gap count is separate from functional pass/fail count in `ProofQuality`\n    40→\n    41→- [x] Task 4: Implement runtime coverage computation in `src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts` (AC: #4)\n    42→  - [x] 4.1: Implement `computeRuntimeCoverage(gapResults: ObservabilityGapResult): RuntimeCoverageResult` -- takes parsed gap data, computes coverage = acsWithLogs / totalACs * 100\n    43→  - [x] 4.2: Implement `saveRuntimeCoverage(projectDir: string, result: RuntimeCoverageResult): Result<void>` -- persists to `sprint-state.json` under `observability.runtime`\n    44→  - [x] 4.3: Follow same atomic write pattern as `coverage.ts` (read-modify-write, temp+rename)\n    45→  - [x] 4.4: Keep file under 150 lines\n    46→\n    47→- [x] Task 5: Wire gap parsing into verify orchestrator (AC: #3)\n    48→  - [x] 5.1: After proof is written and parsed, call `parseObservabilityGaps` on proof content\n    49→  - [x] 5.2: Include observability gap count in `VerifyResult` -- add `observabilityGapCount: number` and `runtimeCoveragePercent: number` fields\n    50→  - [x] 5.3: Report observability gaps separately in verification output (not mixed with functional failures)\n    51→\n    52→- [x] Task 6: Export new types and functions from module barrels (AC: all)\n    53→  - [x] 6.1: Add new type exports to `src/modules/observability/index.ts`: `RuntimeCoverageEntry`, `RuntimeCoverageResult`, `RuntimeCoverageState`\n    54→  - [x] 6.2: Add new function exports: `computeRuntimeCoverage`, `saveRuntimeCoverage`\n    55→  - [x] 6.3: Add `parseObservabilityGaps` export to `src/modules/verify/index.ts`\n    56→\n    57→- [x] Task 7: Write unit tests (AC: all)\n    58→  - [x] 7.1: Create `src/modules/observability/__tests__/runtime-coverage.test.ts`:\n    59→    - Test `computeRuntimeCoverage` with 10 ACs and 7 with logs = 70%\n    60→    - Test `computeRuntimeCoverage` with 0 ACs (edge case, no division by zero)\n    61→    - Test `computeRuntimeCoverage` with all ACs having logs = 100%\n    62→    - Test `computeRuntimeCoverage` with no ACs having logs = 0%\n    63→    - Test `saveRuntimeCoverage` writes to sprint-state.json correctly\n    64→    - Test `saveRuntimeCoverage` preserves existing static coverage data\n    65→  - [x] 7.2: Create or extend `src/modules/verify/__tests__/parser-observability.test.ts`:\n    66→    - Test `parseObservabilityGaps` detects `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` in proof markdown\n    67→    - Test `parseObservabilityGaps` returns correct per-AC gap presence\n    68→    - Test `parseObservabilityGaps` handles proof with no gaps (all clean)\n    69→    - Test `parseObservabilityGaps` handles proof with all gaps\n    70→  - [x] 7.3: Update `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-prompt.test.ts`:\n    71→    - Test that generated prompt includes observability check instructions\n    72→    - Test that observability endpoint URLs are included in query template\n    73→  - [x] 7.4: Mock all filesystem operations -- no real I/O in unit tests\n    74→  - [x] 7.5: Target 100% coverage on all new files\n    75→\n    76→- [x] Task 8: Integration verification (AC: all)\n    77→  - [x] 8.1: Run `npm run build` -- verify tsup compiles new modules\n    78→  - [x] 8.2: Run `npm run test:unit` -- all tests pass\n    79→  - [x] 8.3: Verify module boundaries: only barrel index.ts exports public API\n    80→  - [x] 8.4: Verify no file exceeds 300 lines (NFR9)\n    81→\n    82→## Dev Agent Record\n    83→\n    84→### Implementation Plan\n    85→\n    86→- Task 1: Added `RuntimeCoverageEntry`, `RuntimeCoverageResult`, `RuntimeCoverageState` interfaces to observability types. Extended `ObservabilityCoverageState` with optional `runtime` and `CoverageTargets` with optional `runtimeTarget`.\n    87→- Task 2: Added \"Step 3.5: Observability Check After Each Command\" section to verify-prompt.ts template with VictoriaLogs query and `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag instructions.\n    88→- Task 3: Implemented `parseObservabilityGaps()` in parser.ts that scans proof markdown for `## AC N:` headings and `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tags. Added `ObservabilityGapResult` and `ObservabilityGapEntry` types to verify types.\n    89→- Task 4: Created `runtime-coverage.ts` with `computeRuntimeCoverage()` and `saveRuntimeCoverage()`. Follows same atomic write pattern as coverage.ts. File is 112 lines.\n    90→- Task 5: Added `observabilityGapCount` and `runtimeCoveragePercent` fields to `VerifyResult`. Wired `parseObservabilityGaps` into `verifyStory()` in index.ts. Updated all existing VerifyResult constructions in verify.ts, verifier-session.ts, and verify.test.ts.\n    91→- Task 6: Updated both barrel files with new type and function exports.\n    92→- Task 7: Created runtime-coverage.test.ts (21 tests), parser-observability.test.ts (11 tests), added 3 tests to verify-prompt.test.ts. All filesystem ops mocked.\n    93→- Task 8: Build passes, all 2510 tests pass, module boundaries clean, all files under 300 lines.\n    94→\n    95→### Debug Log\n    96→\n    97→- Import boundary violation: `runtime-coverage.ts` initially imported from `../verify/types.js` (internal file). Fixed to import from `../verify/index.js` (barrel).\n    98→\n    99→### Completion Notes\n   100→\n   101→All 8 tasks and all subtasks implemented. 35 new tests added across 3 test files. Build and full regression suite pass (2510/2510). Runtime coverage types follow architecture Decision 2 (separate metrics). No new dependencies added.\n   102→\n   103→## File List\n   104→\n   105→- src/modules/observability/types.ts (modified) -- added RuntimeCoverageEntry, RuntimeCoverageResult, RuntimeCoverageState; extended ObservabilityCoverageState and CoverageTargets\n   106→- src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts (new) -- computeRuntimeCoverage, saveRuntimeCoverage\n   107→- src/modules/observability/index.ts (modified) -- added new type and function exports\n   108→- src/modules/observability/__tests__/runtime-coverage.test.ts (new) -- 21 unit tests\n   109→- src/modules/verify/types.ts (modified) -- added ObservabilityGapEntry, ObservabilityGapResult, extended VerifyResult\n   110→- src/modules/verify/parser.ts (modified) -- added parseObservabilityGaps function\n   111→- src/modules/verify/index.ts (modified) -- added parseObservabilityGaps export and new type exports\n   112→- src/modules/verify/__tests__/parser-observability.test.ts (new) -- 11 unit tests\n   113→- src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-prompt.test.ts (modified) -- added 3 observability check tests\n   114→- src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify.test.ts (modified) -- updated VerifyResult constructions with new fields\n   115→- src/templates/verify-prompt.ts (modified) -- added Step 3.5 observability check section\n   116→- src/commands/verify.ts (modified) -- added new VerifyResult fields\n   117→- src/lib/verifier-session.ts (modified) -- added new VerifyResult fields\n   118→\n   119→## Change Log\n   120→\n   121→- 2026-03-19: Implemented Story 2.1 -- runtime observability coverage types, verify-prompt observability check instructions, proof gap parser, runtime coverage computation/persistence, verify orchestrator wiring, barrel exports, and comprehensive unit tests.\n   122→\n   123→## Dev Notes\n   124→\n   125→### Architecture References\n   126→\n   127→This story implements architecture Decision 3 (Runtime Validation — Verification IS the Runtime Check). The verifier already runs `docker exec` commands for each AC. This story adds an observability query after each command to detect silent code paths.\n   128→\n   129→Architecture Decision 2 (Separate Metrics) applies: runtime coverage is stored separately from static coverage. The `ObservabilityCoverageState` type from Story 1.3 is extended with a `runtime` section.\n   130→\n   131→### Key Implementation Details\n   132→\n   133→**verify-prompt.ts changes:** The template at `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` already has observability endpoint configuration (`victoriaLogs`, `victoriaMetrics`, `victoriaTraces`). The change is to add explicit instructions for the verifier to query logs after each docker exec, and to use the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag when zero events are found.\n   134→\n   135→**Parser changes:** The `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` already classifies evidence commands (see `EvidenceCommandType` including `'observability'`). This story adds detection of the `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]` tag in proof text, counting gaps per AC.\n   136→\n   137→**Runtime coverage module:** New file `src/modules/observability/runtime-coverage.ts` implements the coverage computation. This is separate from `coverage.ts` (which handles static coverage) per the separation of concerns principle.\n   138→\n   139→**State persistence:** The `observability` section in `sprint-state.json` currently has `static` and `targets` (from Story 1.3). This story adds `runtime` alongside, following the architecture Decision 2 shape.\n   140→\n   141→### Target State Shape in sprint-state.json\n   142→\n   143→After this story, the `observability` section becomes:\n   144→\n   145→```json\n   146→{\n   147→  \"observability\": {\n   148→    \"static\": {\n   149→      \"coveragePercent\": 75,\n   150→      \"lastScanTimestamp\": \"2026-03-19T14:30:00Z\",\n   151→      \"history\": [...]\n   152→    },\n   153→    \"runtime\": {\n   154→      \"coveragePercent\": 70,\n   155→      \"lastValidationTimestamp\": \"2026-03-19T15:00:00Z\",\n   156→      \"modulesWithTelemetry\": 7,\n   157→      \"totalModules\": 10,\n   158→      \"telemetryDetected\": true\n   159→    },\n   160→    \"targets\": {\n   161→      \"staticTarget\": 80,\n   162→      \"runtimeTarget\": 60\n   163→    }\n   164→  }\n   165→}\n   166→```\n   167→\n   168→### Observability Query Approach\n   169→\n   170→Per architecture Decision 3, the verifier queries VictoriaLogs after each `docker exec`:\n   171→\n   172→```\n   173→curl '${victoriaLogs}/select/logsql/query?query=_stream_id:*&start=-30s&limit=100'\n   174→```\n   175→\n   176→If the response contains zero log entries, the verifier tags the AC section with `[OBSERVABILITY GAP]`. The proof parser then counts these tags.\n   177→\n   178→### What This Story Does NOT Include\n   179→\n   180→- No hook enforcement blocking commits on low runtime coverage -- that's Story 2.2\n   181→- No standalone runtime check outside verification -- that's Story 2.3\n   182→- No audit command integration -- that's Epic 3\n   183→- No code review integration -- that's Story 5.1\n   184→- No combined static+runtime metric -- metrics are always reported separately (Decision 2)\n   185→\n   186→### Dependencies\n   187→\n   188→- **Depends on:** Story 1.3 (coverage state types and persistence) -- DONE\n   189→- **Depends on:** Story 1.2 (analyzer module types) -- DONE\n   190→- **Depended on by:** Story 2.2 (hook enforcement reads runtime coverage), Story 2.3 (standalone runtime check reuses runtime coverage computation), Story 5.2 (verification runtime integration)\n   191→\n   192→### File Size Constraint\n   193→\n   194→Each new file must be under 300 lines per NFR9. `runtime-coverage.ts` should be ~100 lines. Parser additions should be ~50 lines within existing file.\n   195→\n   196→### Existing Relevant Code\n   197→\n   198→- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` -- template to modify (currently 174 lines)\n   199→- `src/modules/verify/parser.ts` -- parser to extend\n   200→- `src/modules/verify/types.ts` -- `ProofQuality` and `EvidenceCommandType` already exist\n   201→- `src/modules/observability/coverage.ts` -- static coverage persistence (pattern to follow)\n   202→- `src/modules/observability/types.ts` -- types to extend with runtime types\n   203→- `src/modules/observability/index.ts` -- barrel to update\n   204→\n   205→### References\n   206→\n   207→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 2] -- Separate Metrics, ObservabilityCoverage interface\n   208→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 3] -- Runtime Validation approach\n   209→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md#Decision 6] -- Module structure\n   210→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-operational-excellence.md#Story 2.1] -- Acceptance criteria and user story\n   211→- [Source: src/templates/verify-prompt.ts] -- Verification prompt template\n   212→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts] -- ProofQuality, EvidenceCommandType\n   213→- [Source: src/modules/observability/coverage.ts] -- Static coverage persistence pattern\n   214→\n   215→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   216→## Verification Requirements\n   217→\n   218→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/2-1-verification-observability-check.proof.md`)\n   219→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   220→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100% of all new code in src/)\n   221→\n   222→## Documentation Requirements\n   223→\n   224→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (src/modules/observability/AGENTS.md, src/modules/verify/AGENTS.md)\n   225→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/2-1-verification-observability-check.md`\n   226→\n   227→## Testing Requirements\n   228→\n   229→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   230→- [ ] Filesystem operations mocked (no real I/O in unit tests)\n   231→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   232→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   233→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HBKwqV1bJPP1dmcLZUuumY","session_id":"8712fecb-812b-48fe-bd95-ad6ae808447d","uuid":"d835d31f-d02b-4279-ae7a-0ba64206203c","timestamp":"2026-03-20T05:47:02.601Z"}
